trend_summary: Across the time‐series, warehouses, office blocks and transport infrastructure steadily infilled open lots. Industrial estates coalesced into a continuous corridor, farmland retreated, and woodland buffers appeared along new roads. The airport complex lengthened its runway and added aprons, while upgraded highways improved connectivity. Built footprint roughly doubled, indicating ongoing, medium-intensity suburbanisation.
notable_changes: Industrial/warehouse estates expanded west-to-east, filling former fields.
Airport in the southeast gained a longer runway, extra taxiways and aprons.
New arterial highway and interchanges constructed, improving north–south access.
Agricultural plots in central and western sections converted to built use.
Woodland strips and landscaped green buffers introduced along major roads.
